name: Kenong
desc: Kenong is a collection of hollow “kettles” that placed horizontally and take the secondary role of Gamelan after Gong. Kenong is played together with Kempyang and Kethuk by one player only.

name: Kethuk
desc: Kethuk is a monotone instrument, so it can be used on both scale types

name: Kempyang
desc: Kempyang is similar with kethuk but with different structure. Not all structures used kempyang, but it is never played without the Kethuk.

name: Gong
desc: Gong is a large sized Gong which take the main role of gamelan

name: Gong Suwukan
desc: Gong Suwukan is smaller than Gong, and plays on every music lines called gatra

name: Kempul
desc: Kempul is a collection of mini gongs that plays along the music
